<div class="container">
  <div id="modal-invalid-skill" class="modal fade" role="dialog">
    <div class="modal-dialog">

      <!-- Modal content-->
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
          <h4 class="modal-title">Invalid Skill</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
          <p>You can only add a skill that is already in our directory. If you think we have left out an important skill, please let us know at <a href="mailto:admin@progcode.org">admin@progcode.org</a> .</p>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-6">
      <h1 class="text-center">Volunteer Registration</h1>

      <p class="lead">ProgCode is a 501(c)(4) non-profit, non-partisan, progressive community of volunteers whose mission is to remove or reduce the influence of big money in politics by creating open source technology designed to empower the grassroots.</p>

      <p class="lead">In an effort to balance the safety of the ProgCode community with the privacy of registrants, all information provided on this form is treated as confidential by a three-person internal vetting committee. No personal information provided here will be shared with members of the community or with other individuals or entities. Responses are used only for light vetting and verification to ensure alignment of interests between the registrant and the community.</p>

      <p class="lead">Ready to join Progressive Coders Network? This is where you start!</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row justify-content-center bg-light">
    <div class="col-6 pt-5">
      <% if @user.is_approved %>
        <%= render :partial => "users/approved_form" %>
      <% else %>
        <%= render :partial => "users/form" %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
